<!-- Notes on this file.
   
There is a stanza for each telescope, which is named with "name=". 
For example, this would be HST vs. JWST.

Within each telescope, there are instrument stanzas, each named with "name="  
For example, this would be WFC3 vs. ACS for HST.

Within each instrument, there are multiple detectors, each named with "name=". 
But one also must specify which device within the detector which of the 
devices is to be the reference point.  For example, this would be WFC3/IR vs. 
WFC3UVIS for WFC3.

within each detector, there can be multiple devices.  For exmple, this would 
be WFC3/UVIS CCD1 vs. CCD2.

within each device, there are a host of entries for the grisms that work with 
that device, ways of encoding all the possible extensions, and the siaf info. 
The SIAF info may or may not have SIP coefficeints (if they're known, and 
you ahve them, please put them in.  If not just open and close the stanza 
for "siaf".

Last updated Aug 6, 2020 by RER


 -->

